.TH "cxlflash_disk_virtual_open" 9 "cxlflash_disk_virtual_open" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cxlflash_disk_virtual_open \- open a virtual disk of specified size
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" cxlflash_disk_virtual_open
.BI "(struct scsi_device *sdev "  ","
.BI "void *arg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sdev" 12
SCSI device associated with LUN owning virtual LUN.
.IP "arg" 12
UVirtual ioctl data structure.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
On successful return, the user is informed of the resource handle
to be used to identify the virtual LUN and the size (in blocks) of
the virtual LUN in last LBA format. When the size of the virtual LUN
is zero, the last LBA is reflected as -1.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -errno on failure
